# The Narrator — environment configuration
# This is the LAPTOP backend's config (the orchestrator). The QNX Pi firmware is
# configured separately (it just needs this laptop's host:port — see FIRMWARE_LISTEN).
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. Everything here is free-tier; no payment required.
# Do NOT commit your real .env (see .gitignore).

# --- Firmware ingest (LAN / TCP) -------------------------------------------
# host:port this laptop binds for the Pi's frames + audio + TFLite events.
# The Pi connects here over the LAN (Wi-Fi).
FIRMWARE_LISTEN=0.0.0.0:8765

# --- Deepgram (ears + voice) -----------------------------------------------
# Speech-to-text (STT) and text-to-speech (TTS).
DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=

# --- Anthropic / Claude Haiku (eyes + brain) -------------------------------
# Vision: the camera frame goes straight to Claude Haiku 4.5 (image input),
# which describes the scene AND writes the in-character line in one call.
# (Overshoot is no longer used — Claude vision replaced the "eyes".)
# TFLite runs on-device (Pi firmware) for event triggers — no key needed.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- Redis (memory + state) ------------------------------------------------
# Narration history (callbacks) + shared active personality/mode state.
# e.g. redis://localhost:6379/0
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0

# --- Sentry (reliability) --------------------------------------------------
# Backend error + performance monitoring. Leave blank to disable.
SENTRY_DSN=

# --- Optional / build-last -------------------------------------------------
# Midjourney for the async illustrated journal (off the live path).
# MIDJOURNEY_API_KEY=
